# Environment variables for Contoso Hotels development
# Copy this file to .env and update the values

# SQL Server password - change this to a secure password
SQL_PASSWORD=your_secure_password_here

# AI Concierge Configuration
# Azure AI Foundry (Preferred - will be used if both are configured)
AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your-azure-openai-api-key-here
AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource-name.openai.azure.com/

# OpenAI (Fallback - will be used if Azure is not configured)
OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key-here

# Development Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file and rename it to .env
# 2. Configure either Azure AI Foundry OR OpenAI (Azure is preferred):
#    - For Azure AI Foundry: Set AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY and AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT
#    - For OpenAI: Set OPENAI_API_KEY
# 3. Set SQL_PASSWORD for database access
# 4. Run the application: dotnet run

# Production Configuration:
# In production, set these environment variables through your hosting platform:
# - Azure App Service: Application Settings
# - Docker: Environment variables in docker-compose.yml or Dockerfile
# - Kubernetes: ConfigMaps and Secrets

# Notes:
# - Azure AI Foundry endpoints are preferred for enterprise deployments
# - The application will automatically use Azure if configured, otherwise fallback to OpenAI
# - Both providers support the same AI models and capabilities
